name: Waste Master Recycling Services
product_desc: Briquette charcoal and plastic pavement tile are product from waste master recycling Services.Deforestation for the purpose of wood charcoal is creating huge environmental and a pressure to our reserved forests.WRS(SL) charcoal briquette give our customer the alternative to use clean and cheaper energy  for cooking as compared to the traditional wood charcoal.This charcoal briquette is  long lasting ,smokeless,cost friendly,and Eco-friendly, It is produce mainly from varieties of waste  material which in other words help solve the problem of waste management.The second product is plastic paving tile  is done from recycling waste plastic which is also cheaper compared to create paving brick they are durable as plastic take long time to decompose. Both product are good for the middle income family especially the urban poor.
markets: Clean Energy, Product Design, Waste Management, Cleaning

name: WARC Group
product_desc:
We are a food production and agricultural advisory services company. We provide information, services and market access to thousands of smallholder farmers who are below subsistence, and seek to improve their economic output and livelihood. 
We have developed the basic prototype of an application that will act as a service, knowledge and data platform that will revolutionise interaction with dispersed smallholder farmers. We envision this to expand beyond agricultural information, to services such as finance and medical, as we map out and build a new dimension of data points on a previously underserved and underdeveloped part of our community.
high_concept: Private sector sustainable agricultural development for smallholder farmers

product_desc: We sell the only locally produced, branded premium rice in Sierra Leone. We work with smallholder farmers to improve their productivity and incomes.
high_concept: Using smart business and technology to lead Africa's agricultural revolution

name: Wild Diamond Safari
product_desc: The concept is to build two sites with 3000 sq. ft. lodges and detached 500 sq.ft. bungalows, one on the sugar sand beachfront of Sherbro Island in Bonthe District and one in the diamond fields along the Sewa River in Bo District for the 2016/17 season. Itineraries will provide daily excursions to mining sites to look for diamonds during the "kick", as well as buying opportunities at various diamond offices, for tourist wanting to learn more about and experience first hand the intriguing world of the rough diamond trade. Beyond the diamond buying and excursions there are also numerous other sightseeing tours and adventure opportunities within the country.
high_concept: Exotic, luxury eco-tour and one-of-a-kind  excursions for rough diamonds.
markets: Travel & Tourism, Luxury, Fine Jewelry, Entertainment And Luxury Travel

name: B-Gifted
product_desc: B-Gifted lets you have access to innovative learning tools that help build life skills, promote education and raise awareness on peace, human rights and development issues. The product offers new possibilities for access to learning for learners with disability.The product shows the potentials of ICT in delivering educational services and the creation of an inclusive society. The product uses ICT to assist those who have previously detached themselves from society due to their war-induced disability. The product provides a unique learning and sharing experience, and builds trust and life-skills enabling the beneficiaries to reach out to others across the world and become global citizens. The project plays a key role in using ICT for education and for social advantage and benefits and fosters cultural exchange and educational tools for a large number of these disabled persons and creating social relations amongst the local people and an  inclusive society.
markets: Digital Media, Education, ICT, Ict4 D

product_desc: B-Gifted helps children to use creative and technology (innovative education) approaches for peace building and educational development. Recently, B-Gifted has expanded it's work to help victims of amputation in Sierra Leone's war use digital technology for education and humanitarian purposes
high_concept: Innovative education for all the children of Sierra Leone
markets: Mobile, Digital Media, Telecommunications, Underserved Children

name: Samshi Afrika
product_desc:
Samshi Afrika Limited is setting up a 150,000 metric ton steel and power manufacturing unit in Sierra Leone. 

The company will manufacture steel reinforcing bars (re-bar) that are essential to infrastructure development â€“ buildings, roads, bridges etc. Re-bar, used in reinforcing concrete, forms the basis of most infrastructure and construction projects.

The company will also generate 30MW of power using three sources - 16MW from waste heat, 4MW from waste char and 10MW of thermal power.
status: Good progress on all fronts over the past few months. Phase II of the project should begin by end of the year
